org.apache.iceberg.encryption

Interface EncryptedInputFile


  • public interface EncryptedInputFile
    Thin wrapper around an InputFile instance that is encrypted.

    The EncryptionManager takes instances of these and uses the attached keyMetadata() to find an encryption key and decrypt the enclosed encryptedInputFile().

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      InputFile encryptedInputFile()
      The InputFile that is reading raw encrypted bytes from the underlying file system.
      EncryptionKeyMetadata keyMetadata()
      Metadata pointing to some encryption key that would be used to decrypt the input file provided by encryptedInputFile().
